&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;CLEAR is building THE secure identity company of the future. Our mission is to make experiences safer and easier—physically and digitally. With more than 38 million Members and a growing network of partners across the world, CLEAR&#39;s secure identity platform is transforming the way people live, work, and travel. Whether it’s at the airport, stadium, or throughout your everyday life, CLEAR unlocks the magic of frictionless experiences.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re hiring a Product Lead to lead the evolution of our identity and evidence platform powering both CLEAR Travel and &lt;a href=&quot;https://identity.clearme.com/&quot;&gt;CLEAR1&lt;/a&gt;. This role is responsible for evolving the systems that establish, maintain, and leverage high-integrity identity across consumer and enterprise experiences—enabling seamless, secure interactions wherever CLEAR operates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Own the Identity Verification Platform&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the strategy and roadmap for CLEAR’s identity and evidence platform across consumer (CLEAR+) and enterprise (CLEAR1) products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build reusable proofing, verification, and evidence services that power all CLEAR surfaces (mobile, web, airport, partner integrations)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Advance Identity Assurance &amp;amp; Evidence Systems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expand and optimize source verification to improve assurance, reduce cost, and increase coverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define how identity is established (proofing) vs. continuously evaluated (signals), and evolve both layers over time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive alignment with National Institute of Standards and Technology frameworks (e.g., IAL2/IAL3) while maintaining flexibility for real-world use cases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Build a Scalable, Reusable Identity Layer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Decouple identity from individual products—ensuring identity can be created once and leveraged across multiple experiences and relying parties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop systems for evidence storage, re-use, and auditability to support network-level advantages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure interoperability with emerging standards (e.g., mDoc / ISO 18013-7)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Optimize Cost, Performance, and Resiliency&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive down cost per proofing/verification through orchestration, vendor strategy, and intelligent fallback systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve success rates and reduce false negatives/positives across all identity flows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build resiliency into critical identity services to support high-scale, real-time environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Own Data Integrity, Observability, and Compliance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Treat data integrity and traceability as first-class requirements across all identity systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build reporting, alerting, and audit tooling across all assurance layers and dependencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure systems are proactively compliant with regulatory and audit requirements—not reactive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Drive Cross-Platform Experiences&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
